From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000004 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: wheetazlab <ops@wheetazlab.com>
Date: Mon, 05 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] Revert "PCI: pcie-brcmstb: fake MSIx support on internal MSI target"

Commit 831b46008fa48ec756bc1ddc66ab9e75207d05b9 added MSI_FLAG_PCI_MSIX
to BRCM_MSI_FLAGS_SUPPORTED, enabling "fake" MSI-X via the BRCM internal
MSI target register.  On BCM2712 (CM5/CM4) with NVMe storage, this causes
a boot-time crash: the NVMe driver switches to the MSI-X allocation path,
but the BRCM internal MSI controller (32 vectors, single target address)
is not a valid MSI-X parent for NVMe and conflicts with the dedicated
BCM2712 MIP MSI-X hardware controller.

The pre-existing path (MSI only, no MSI_FLAG_PCI_MSIX) works correctly on
all known CM5 + NVMe configurations (tested with rpi-6.12.y stable).

Reverts the single-line addition.  Does not touch any other part of the
Apr 20 2026 pcie-brcmstb patch series.

Refs: 831b46008fa48ec756bc1ddc66ab9e75207d05b9
---
 drivers/pci/controller/pcie-brcmstb.c | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-brcmstb.c b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-brcmstb.c
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-brcmstb.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-brcmstb.c
@@ -666,8 +666,7 @@ static void brcm_pcie_set_outbound_win(struct brcm_pcie *pcie,
 				 MSI_FLAG_NO_AFFINITY)
 
 #define BRCM_MSI_FLAGS_SUPPORTED (MSI_GENERIC_FLAGS_MASK	| \
-				  MSI_FLAG_MULTI_PCI_MSI	| \
-				  MSI_FLAG_PCI_MSIX)
+				  MSI_FLAG_MULTI_PCI_MSI)
 
 static const struct msi_parent_ops brcm_msi_parent_ops = {
 	.required_flags		= BRCM_MSI_FLAGS_REQUIRED,
